node.text:
Congratulations to the winner of our 2021 Matador Trips Palawan giveaway @ianlauerastro! 🥳 — Here is a sneak peek of what the trip will be like, I can’t wait to be here sailing with you and your +1🙌🏼.
⠀
If you didn’t win, no worries — There are still a few spots available on the Palawan trip for purchase and @matadornetwork is offering a limited time 20% off your ENTIRE trip! Just head to www.matadornetwork.com/trips/ to check out the Palawan trip, or the 5 other awesome adventures @matadornetwork are planning!⁣
⠀
I’m so excited for a tropical getaway and would love to have you join us! If not, stay tuned for more awesome giveaways in 2021!
 #travelstoke #matadornetwork #palawan

node.text:
Our house is starting to look like a home!

After spending so much time designing a 3D model on a computer it’s wild to watch it come to life! 
@iconwoodworking did such an incredible job on this super custom design. 
The reclaimed teak stair treads by @indoteakdesign really complement the cabinets and we can’t wait to install the teak countertop!

#tinyhousebuild #tinyhouse

node.text:
TOMORROW is International Go Skateboarding Day! This small piece of wood on wheels has always been one of my biggest passions. Here is a mix of old and new footage, some of which is me jumping down stairs and rails back in the day and is why my body feels like I’m 70 yrs old now 😂👨🏼‍🦳.

But whether you’re flowing down a sidewalk, or jumping down rails, I’ve always loved the self expression, art, and confidence that being on a board can bring.

Huge thanks to @Sector9 for supporting my passion and also putting my images on the bottom of their boards, definitely a dream come true! 

If you have a board, get out there and have some fun tomorrow! 🙌🏼🛹

node.text:
We just got back from an amazing trip sailing through the Caribbean! Laysea and I were mostly shooting video for a work project but it was fun to snap a few photos along the way!

The whole experience was awesome and I’ll probably share a few more photos or videos but I’m excited to get back to building our tiny house after 2+ months of traveling for work. 🤓🏠🔨

#virginislands #boatlife #underwaterphotography

node.text:
We’re off to the Tropics! 🏝

This is our first time leaving the continent in over a year and I’m so excited that the destination has warm, clear water & open seas!

If you haven’t noticed by now, gear layouts are by far my favorite way to pack for a trip 🤓 If there’s anything you’re curious about in the #knolling shot, drop a question in comments!

Out of everything, I’m probably most excited to be testing out the new EDGE water housing from @aquatech_imagingsolutions! Hopefully I can still remember how to swim and hold my breath, it’s been a while haha.

node.text:
Happy Earth Day 🌎🌱. 
Our home is more beautiful than words can describe and as I’ve continued to learn and see first hand how fragile it is, I’ve been making very conscious efforts to shift my lifestyle while also surrounding myself with people and brands that are working hard to make the world a better place! 

These are a few images I captured of some of my close friends and favorite women in the community who are taking a stand and helping to educate people (including myself) on all kinds of important topics. This shoot was for @sea.and.soil & @billabongwomens who are announcing some really awesome initiatives today. Go check it out! 

Also, huge thanks to @changingtidesfoundation for selecting me to be their first male ambassador. I’m honored to be part of the team and will continue to learn more, give back, and help educate and hopefully inspire others to respect and protect our Mother Earth 🙏🏼.
#respectandprotect #seaandsoil #billabongwomens

node.text:
It’s my birthday which officially marks 7 years since I took off in my grandma’s old van to chase my dreams! For a quiet, introverted person it was a complete leap of faith, especially at that time, when there was almost no info on van life. I never thought my images and my story would reach so many people around the world and I am continually humbled and appreciative of that.

Huge thank you to everyone who has followed my journey and helped make my dreams possible! This app has been a big part of my journey and social media has become both a blessing and a curse to myself and millions of people around the world. 

My goal has always been to encourage people to get outside, to inspire them to push past their comfort zones, to respect and appreciate Mother Nature, and to follow their passions. I hope my actions and my images can continue to inspire others to do the same, even in some small way!

Thanks again, and I hope you all have an awesome day.
Live passionately, follow your dreams!

node.text:
Yesterday’s incredible hike! 
 
We had to plan a month in advance to get the shuttle pass since cars aren’t allowed at the trailhead this time of year, so we really lucked out with perfect weather conditions this time! 

This has always been one of my favorite day hikes in a National Park, have you done it or would you like to?

Friendly reminder 🤓: This is one of the more dangerous National Park hikes, and while these chains are installed throughout the the trail for assistance, it’s imperative to wear proper shoes, be cautious, and know your limits.
Safe adventuring!

@gypsealaysea @gopro @hippytree
@undercanvasofficial
#utah #hippytree #undercanvas #gopro

node.text:
I’d driven this trail several times but only ever dreamt about photographing it.
⠀
Laysea & I woke up hours before sunrise to be able to get out to location & get the shot. She was several hundred feet below me (but roughly an 8 mile drive) and I was up on top the canyon with my camera when the truck seized up in 1st gear. (What a relief that we’d been using walkie talkie to coordinate composition!)
She was able to put it into 2nd and drive out, but the problem progressed once we got into town to the point the truck wasn’t drivable.
One $500 tow, a hotel room, a large pizza & three mechanics later, I am so grateful to find out it was as simple as an over-tightened brake during the truck’s service just prior to this trip.
The highs & lows of life on the road are emotional, sometimes challenging, but always rewarding. I am happy to report, we are #ontheroadagain.
__________________________
UPDATE: I wrote this last night after editing the photo, but this morning the issue happened again 😭. Ultimately the self adjusting brake mechanism continued to tighten the brakes to the point the truck wouldn’t move forward. My home mechanic guided me via FaceTime to remove the system for the remainder of this trip, and we are, again, back on the road 😬🤪
